==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inebriation
<hw>In*e`bri*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inebriatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The condition of being inebriated;
intoxication; figuratively, deprivation of sense and judgment by
anything that exhilarates, as success.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Preserve him from the <qex>inebriation</qex> of prosperity.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Drunkenness</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inebriety</ent>⟦br⟧
